@OmarBasem : can you confirm which fleet you are connected to?
At the moment status.prod fleet works for me on mobile simulator when desktop app is terminated.

<img width="287" alt="Screenshot 2022-12-21 at 1 00 28 PM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/64726664/208846205-06b9d229-82a3-46db-af36-0e7c8d3c614b.png">

> [Wed Dec 21 2022 08:45:11.449]  ERROR    ERROR [status-im.chat.models.loading:58] - failed loading messages test {:code -32000, :message "sql: Scan error on column index 18, name \"album_id\": converting NULL to string is unsupported"}

I believe there's a fix for this in status-go https://github.com/status-im/status-go/commit/b1ff13eb7d9ccaa9beecc4cd3ca0c103a83e3950 , but yes, the issue is that album-id could be empty, so we should either do that or use sql.NulString cc @OmarBasem 

The issue about status-desktop and mobile, is that both try to bind UDP port 9000, that's for discovery, and so they can't run on the same machine (I believe you can use ENV variable on desktop to set the port cc @richard-ramos ), but we should fix this, I don't think there's any reason why we want to run discovery on 9k, we should probably use a random port ideally, if that's possible (i.e pass 0), but I don't believe that's supported.
